Comment: black_tie_hair said "BLACK TIE HAIR DISTRIBUTOR was founded by entrepreneur Mrs. Deborah Odom in 1999 in Apple Valley, Ca. With over 15 years in the business and over four hundred steady clients, Mrs. Odom was determined to start a company offering A-List quality hair and affordable prices. She has a long love affair with hair.

Black Tie Hair provides its clientele with 100% virgin cuticle hair coming directly from donors in Indian Temples, Brazil and Cambodia. We DO NOT sell any hair from China or Asia. Each strand is handpicked and sorted for the best quality and texture to ensure our clientele is provided with true virgin hair that stands apart from other hair vendors.

Black Tie Hair is unprocessed hair that has not been chemically treated in any way. There are no permanent/semi-permanent colors, perms, or relaxers used to alter color, texture or curl pattern of hair. Our hair comes in natural textures, Straight, Wavy and Curly and in natural color tones of black and brown. Black Tie Hair can be colored using permanent /semi-permanent and cellophane coloring products without losing its natural texture, no tangling and excessive shedding. 
WE ğŸ’š CUSTOMERS !!
#BLACKTIEHAIR #SINCE1999 #NOTNEWTOTHIS #TRUETOTHEHAIRGAME"

Comment: msdeborah55 said "BLACK TIE HAIR DISTRIBUTOR was founded by entrepreneur Mrs. Deborah Odom in 1999 in Apple Valley, Ca. With over 15 years in the business and over four hundred steady clients, Mrs. Odom was determined to start a company offering A-List quality hair and affordable prices. She has a long love affair with hair.

Black Tie Hair provides its clientele with 100% virgin cuticle hair coming directly from donors in Indian Temples, Brazil and Cambodia. We DO NOT sell any hair from China or Asia. Each strand is handpicked and sorted for the best quality and texture to ensure our clientele is provided with true virgin hair that stands apart from other hair vendors.

Black Tie Hair is unprocessed hair that has not been chemically treated in any way. There are no permanent/semi-permanent colors, perms, or relaxers used to alter color, texture or curl pattern of hair. Our hair comes in natural textures, Straight, Wavy and Curly and in natural color tones of black and brown. Black Tie Hair can be colored using permanent /semi-permanent and cellophane coloring products without losing its natural texture, no tangling and excessive shedding. 
WE ğŸ’š OUR CUSTOMERS!!! FOLLOW MY BUSINESS PAGE FOR SPECIALS & UPCOMING EVENTS @black_tie_hair @black_tie_hair @black_tie_hair @black_tie_hair @black_tie_hair"

Comment: _ashleyseeger said "One of the winners of my last 10 Week challenge!! We began before the holidays to show that we can get through holidays and enjoy them without deprivation! It is all about balance and a new way to live! Congrats Jason! 
From Jason, 
What an awesome 10 week challenge!  I canâ€™t thank Ashley enough for her guidance and support.  I am proud and surprised at how far I have come in 10 weeks with the plan Ashley created!  I was surprised by how much fun and encouraging it was to have the support of the entire group of challenge participants!  We were all in it together. 
Before the challenge, I had been dealing with a nagging injury and ultimately used it as an excuse to be unmotivated and undisciplined with my diet and almost non-existent gym attendance.  I heard about the 10 week challenge from a post that Ashley put on her Becoming Badass Facebook page and thought it would be a good chance to lose a few pounds.  From the start, working with Ashley has been awesome!  She was so supportive and made herself available to answer all my questions; and I asked a lot of questions!  The exercise plan was both fun and challenging, which kept me motivated and excited through the end.  I loved how the plan evolved throughout the 10 weeks and really pushed my body at every stage. Coming off my injury, Ashley was very helpful in giving me modifications for some of the exercises.  The diet information was completely laid out and easy to follow.  It was easy to shop and prep food per the diet guidelines.  I could see and feel how well my body responded to the change in diet.  Ashley taught me how to adjust to a healthier life style, not just a quick fad diet. 
I am so glad I participated, and so grateful for the diet/exercise guidance and information.  Thank you for supporting and pushing me to work hard, get stronger, and transform my body! #transformation #challengewinner #progress #winner #becomingbadass #makeyourselfproud"

Ashley taught me how to adjust to a healthier life style, not just a quick fad diet.

Comment: _ashleyseeger said "One of the winners of my last 10 Week challenge!! We began before the holidays to show that we can get through holidays and enjoy them without deprivation! It is all about balance and a new way to live! Congrats Jason! 
From Jason, 
What an awesome 10 week challenge!  I canâ€™t thank Ashley enough for her guidance and support.  I am proud and surprised at how far I have come in 10 weeks with the plan Ashley created!  I was surprised by how much fun and encouraging it was to have the support of the entire group of challenge participants!  We were all in it together. 
Before the challenge, I had been dealing with a nagging injury and ultimately used it as an excuse to be unmotivated and undisciplined with my diet and almost non-existent gym attendance.  I heard about the 10 week challenge from a post that Ashley put on her Becoming Badass Facebook page and thought it would be a good chance to lose a few pounds.  From the start, working with Ashley has been awesome!  She was so supportive and made herself available to answer all my questions; and I asked a lot of questions!  The exercise plan was both fun and challenging, which kept me motivated and excited through the end.  I loved how the plan evolved throughout the 10 weeks and really pushed my body at every stage. Coming off my injury, Ashley was very helpful in giving me modifications for some of the exercises.  The diet information was completely laid out and easy to follow.  It was easy to shop and prep food per the diet guidelines.  I could see and feel how well my body responded to the change in diet.  Ashley taught me how to adjust to a healthier life style, not just a quick fad diet. 
I am so glad I participated, and so grateful for the diet/exercise guidance and information.  Thank you for supporting and pushing me to work hard, get stronger, and transform my body! #transformation #challengewinner #progress #winner #becomingbadass #makeyourselfproud"

Comment: _ashleyseeger said "One of the winners of my last 10 Week challenge!! We began before the holidays to show that we can get through holidays and enjoy them without deprivation! It is all about balance and a new way to live! Congrats Jason! 
From Jason, 
What an awesome 10 week challenge!  I canâ€™t thank Ashley enough for her guidance and support.  I am proud and surprised at how far I have come in 10 weeks with the plan Ashley created!  I was surprised by how much fun and encouraging it was to have the support of the entire group of challenge participants!  We were all in it together. 
Before the challenge, I had been dealing with a nagging injury and ultimately used it as an excuse to be unmotivated and undisciplined with my diet and almost non-existent gym attendance.  I heard about the 10 week challenge from a post that Ashley put on her Becoming Badass Facebook page and thought it would be a good chance to lose a few pounds.  From the start, working with Ashley has been awesome!  She was so supportive and made herself available to answer all my questions; and I asked a lot of questions!  The exercise plan was both fun and challenging, which kept me motivated and excited through the end.  I loved how the plan evolved throughout the 10 weeks and really pushed my body at every stage. Coming off my injury, Ashley was very helpful in giving me modifications for some of the exercises.  The diet information was completely laid out and easy to follow.  It was easy to shop and prep food per the diet guidelines.  I could see and feel how well my body responded to the change in diet.  Ashley taught me how to adjust to a healthier life style, not just a quick fad diet. 
I am so glad I participated, and so grateful for the diet/exercise guidance and information.  Thank you for supporting and pushing me to work hard, get stronger, and transform my body! #transformation #challengewinner #progress #winner #becomingbadass #makeyourselfproud"

Comment: _ashleyseeger said "One of the winners of my last 10 Week challenge!! We began before the holidays to show that we can get through holidays and enjoy them without deprivation! It is all about balance and a new way to live! Congrats Jason! 
From Jason, 
What an awesome 10 week challenge!  I canâ€™t thank Ashley enough for her guidance and support.  I am proud and surprised at how far I have come in 10 weeks with the plan Ashley created!  I was surprised by how much fun and encouraging it was to have the support of the entire group of challenge participants!  We were all in it together. 
Before the challenge, I had been dealing with a nagging injury and ultimately used it as an excuse to be unmotivated and undisciplined with my diet and almost non-existent gym attendance.  I heard about the 10 week challenge from a post that Ashley put on her Becoming Badass Facebook page and thought it would be a good chance to lose a few pounds.  From the start, working with Ashley has been awesome!  She was so supportive and made herself available to answer all my questions; and I asked a lot of questions!  The exercise plan was both fun and challenging, which kept me motivated and excited through the end.  I loved how the plan evolved throughout the 10 weeks and really pushed my body at every stage. Coming off my injury, Ashley was very helpful in giving me modifications for some of the exercises.  The diet information was completely laid out and easy to follow.  It was easy to shop and prep food per the diet guidelines.  I could see and feel how well my body responded to the change in diet.  Ashley taught me how to adjust to a healthier life style, not just a quick fad diet. 
I am so glad I participated, and so grateful for the diet/exercise guidance and information.  Thank you for supporting and pushing me to work hard, get stronger, and transform my body! #transformation #challengewinner #progress #winner #becomingbadass #makeyourselfproud"

Comment: black_tie_hair said "BLACK TIE HAIR DISTRIBUTOR was founded by entrepreneur Mrs. Deborah Odom in 1999 in Apple Valley, Ca. With over 15 years in the business and over four hundred steady clients, Mrs. Odom was determined to start a company offering A-List quality hair and affordable prices. She has a long love affair with hair.

Black Tie Hair provides its clientele with 100% virgin cuticle hair coming directly from donors in Indian Temples, Brazil and Cambodia. We DO NOT sell any hair from China or Asia. Each strand is handpicked and sorted for the best quality and texture to ensure our clientele is provided with true virgin hair that stands apart from other hair vendors.

Black Tie Hair is unprocessed hair that has not been chemically treated in any way. There are no permanent/semi-permanent colors, perms, or relaxers used to alter color, texture or curl pattern of hair. Our hair comes in natural textures, Straight, Wavy and Curly and in natural color tones of black and brown. Black Tie Hair can be colored using permanent /semi-permanent and cellophane coloring products without losing its natural texture, no tangling and excessive shedding."

Comment: msdeborah55 said "BLACK TIE HAIR DISTRIBUTOR was founded by entrepreneur Mrs. Deborah Odom in 1999 in Apple Valley, Ca. With over 15 years in the business and over four hundred steady clients, Mrs. Odom was determined to start a company offering A-List quality hair and affordable prices. She has a long love affair with hair.

Black Tie Hair provides its clientele with 100% virgin cuticle hair coming directly from donors in Indian Temples, Brazil and Cambodia. We DO NOT sell any hair from China or Asia. Each strand is handpicked and sorted for the best quality and texture to ensure our clientele is provided with true virgin hair that stands apart from other hair vendors.

Black Tie Hair is unprocessed hair that has not been chemically treated in any way. There are no permanent/semi-permanent colors, perms, or relaxers used to alter color, texture or curl pattern of hair. Our hair comes in natural textures, Straight, Wavy and Curly and in natural color tones of black and brown. Black Tie Hair can be colored using permanent /semi-permanent and cellophane coloring products without losing its natural texture, no tangling and excessive shedding."
